arts.ttl: England 2-0 Serbia: Arsenal stars on target as Three Lions maintain perfect qualifying record
arts.sum: Bukayo Saka and Eberechi Eze both net stylish goals at Wembley as Thomas Tuchel’s side make it seven wins from seven in Group K

arts.ttl: Saka and Eze strikes sink Serbia as England maintain perfect World Cup qualifying record
arts.sum: It was down to England’s consistency and the paucity of the opposition in World Cup qualifying Group K that there was zero jeopardy about this occasion. Thomas Tuchel’s team can only beat what is in front of them and they had done that with sufficient regularity to guarantee their place at the finals next summer with two matches to spare. It made for the question. Could they do it on a soggy midweek night when most of the people outside their camp did not care? The answer was yes, even if it was not a performance or an occasion to quicken the pulse or live for any length of time in the memory. The serious business is to come. Continue reading...

arts.ttl: England player ratings vs Serbia: Bukayo Saka brilliant as Jude Bellingham proves point
arts.sum: A promising debut from Nico O’Reilly at Wembley as Eberechi Eze and Phil Foden impress off the bench

arts.ttl: Bukayo Saka volleys away Thomas Tuchel’s criticism as England see off Serbia in World Cup qualifying
arts.sum: England 2-0 Serbia: Arsenal players scored both goals at Wembley as Saka and his Gunners teammate Eberechi Eze secured three more points for the Three Lions

arts.ttl: England's stunning strikes extend winning record as Serbia's World Cup hopes are dashed
arts.sum: England extend their winning record in World Cup qualifying to seven straight games with a comfortable 2-0 win over Serbia thanks to two stunning strikes.

arts.ttl: England player ratings: Elliot Anderson and Eberchi Eze impress in World Cup qualifying win over Serbia
arts.sum: England saw off Serbia to continue their dominance of World Cup qualifying

arts.ttl: England beat Serbia to maintain 100 per cent World Cup qualifying record
arts.sum: Arsenal pair Bukayo Saka and Eberechi Eze were on target in Thursday’s Wembley win.

arts.ttl: Saka and Eze steer England past Serbia
arts.sum: Bukayo Saka and Eberechi Eze scored as England beat Serbia 2-0 in their World Cup qualifier.

arts.ttl: Saka and Eze strike as England beat Serbia after Tuchel intervention
arts.sum: England maintained their perfect World Cup qualifying record with a 2-0 win over Serbia thanks to a fine Bukayo Saka volley and excellent Eberechi Eze finish, as Jude Bellingham and Phil Foden had mixed performances off the bench at Wembley.

arts.ttl: England beat Serbia as stars take chance to impress Thomas Tuchel - 6 talking points
arts.sum: ENGLAND 2-0 SERBIA: Brilliant goals from Bukayo Saka and Eberechi Eze were enough to see England extend their brilliant qualifying run for next summer's World Cup under Thomas Tuchel
